ef>\n| GI = 9.25/10<ref name=\"gameinformerreview\">\n{{cite web|title=New Super Mario Bros. U Review|publisher=gameinformer|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/new_super_mario_bros_u/b/wii_u/archive/2012/11/18/new-super-mario-bros-u-review.aspx|date=November 18, 2012|accessdate=December 9, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121121164506/http://www.gameinformer.com/games/new_super_mario_bros_u/b/wii_u/archive/2012/11/18/new-super-mario-bros-u-review.aspx|archive-date=2012-11-21|url-status=live}}\n</ref>\n| GMaster = 82%<ref name=\"gamesmasterreview\">\n{{cite web |url=http://www.gamepur.com/news/9650-first-review-new-super-mario-bros-u-and-nintendo-land-arrived.html |title=First review of New Super Mario Bros. U and Nintendo Land arrived |date=November 5, 2012 |accessdate=November 5, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150623195256/http://www.gamepur.com/news/9650-first-review-new-super-mario-bros-u-and-nintendo-land-arrived.html |archive-date=2015-06-23 |url-status=live }}\n</ref>\n| GSpot = (Wii U) 8.5/10<ref name=\"GS\">\n{{cite web |author=Peter Brown |url=http://www.gamespot.com/new-super-mario-bros-u/reviews/new-super-mario-bros-u-review-6400232/ |title=New Super Mario Bros. U Review |publisher=GameSpot |date=November 18, 2012 |accessdate=August 16, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130811065046/http://www.gamespot.com/new-super-mario-bros-u/reviews/new-super-mario-bros-u-review-6400232/ |archive-date=2013-08-11 |url-status=live }}\n</ref><br /> (NS) 7/10<ref>\n{{cite web|last=Dayus|first=Oscar|url=https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/new-super-mario-bros-u-deluxe-review-its-a-me-agai/1900-6417061/|title=New Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe Review|publisher=GameSpot|date=January 9, 2019|accessdate=January 9, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190110073829/https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/new-super-mario-bros-u-deluxe-review-its-a-me-agai/1900-6417061/|archive-date=2019-01-10|url-status=live}}\n</ref>\n| GB = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"giantbombreview\">\n{{cite web |url=http://www.giantbomb.com/new-super-mario-bros-u/61-35574/reviews/ |title=New Super Mario Bros. U Review |accessdate=November 18, 2012 |publisher=Giant Bomb |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120014039/http://www.giantbomb.com/new-super-mario-bros-u/61-35574/reviews/ |archive-date=2012-11-20 |url-status=live }}\n</ref>\n| IGN = (Wii U) 9.1/10<ref name=\"ignreview\">\n{{cite web|title=New Super Mario Bros. Wii U Review|publisher=IGN|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/11/15/new-super-mario-bros-u-review|date=November 15, 2012|accessdate=November 15, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121115190738/http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/11/15/new-super-mario-bros-u-review|archive-date=2012-11-15|url-status=live}}\n</ref><br />(NS) 8/10<ref>{{cite web|last=Ogilvie|first=Tristan|url=https://uk.ign.com/articles/2019/01/09/new-super-mario-bros-u-deluxe-review|title=New Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe Review|date=January 9, 2019|accessdate=January 9, 2019}}</ref>\n| Joystiq = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=\"joystiqreview\">\n{{cite web |url=http://www.joystiq.com/2012/11/15/new-super-mario-bros-u-review/ |title=New Super Mario Bros. U review: A return to form |accessdate=November 15, 2012 |publisher=Joystiq |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121118053042/http://www.joystiq.com/2012/11/15/new-super-mario-bros-u-review |archive-date=2012-11-18 |url-status=live }}\n</ref>\n| ONM = 86%\n| NWR = 9.5/10<ref>\n{{cite web|url=http://www.nintendoworldreport.com/review/32569/new-super-mario-bros-u-wii-u|title=New Super Mario Bros. U review|publisher=Nintendo World Report|accessdate=November 21, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140602050933/http://www.nintendoworldreport.com/review/32569/new-super-mario-bros-u-wii-u|archive-date=2014-06-02|url-status=live}}\n</ref>\n}}\n''New Super Mario Bros. U'' was positively received by critics. ''GamesMaster'' magazine called it \"a great excuse for families to gather round the TV, and an enticing glimpse of Mario's HD future\".<ref name=\"gamesmasterreview\"/>\n[[IGN]] stated that \"Nintendo's approach here strikes a great balance in all areas, ranging from its difficulty to design to enemies and bosses\".<ref name=\"ignreview\"/> ''[[Joystiq]]'' commented \"There's a sense of wonder again, of exploration and discovery. I'm not quite prepared to say ''New Super Mario Bros. U'' fully recaptures the spark of Mario's 2D heyday, but it's an impressive step in the right direction\".<ref name=\"joystiqreview\"/> ''[[Game Informer]]'' considers it the best game in the ''New Super Mario Bros.'' series, saying it has \"Some of the most creative ''NSMB'' levels Nintendo has created\".<ref name=\"gameinformerreview\"/> [[GameSpot]] observes \"It's a challenging platformer, an excellent recreation of Mario's best moments, and it's the perfect way to kick-off Nintendo's journey into HD.\"<ref name=\"GS\"/> SupeReal Media gave the game an 'A' Grade, praising the versatility, and stating that Mario has never looked so good.<ref>{{cite web |last=Hradsky |first=Brian |url=http://superealmedia.com/2014/01/01/game-reviews-new-super-mario-bros-wii-u/ |title=Game Reviews \"New Super Mario Bros. Wii U\" |publisher=SupeReal Media |date=January 21, 2014 |accessdate=March 2, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140102192423/http://superealmedia.com/2014/01/01/game-reviews-new-super-mario-bros-wii-u/ |archive-date=January 2, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n[[Giant Bomb]] was slightly more critical, noting \"Everything about ''New Super Mario Bros. U'' is pretty exciting, except the game itself. Is it possible that this is the best game in the 'New' series to date--not to mention one of the best exclusive Wii U games on the market, by default\u2014and at the same time kind of flatly uninteresting? Apparently so. The game is perfectly well made for what it is, and I had plenty of fun playing it in short bursts here and there, but at this point the series' by-the-numbers design philosophy is starting to lend the name 'New Super Mario Bros.' a degree of unintentional irony\".<ref name=\"giantbombreview\"/>\nAt the 10th Annual [[VGX (award show)|Spike Video Game Awards]] on [[Spike (TV network)|Spike]], ''New Super Mario Bros. U'' won \"Best Wii/Wii U Game\".\n\n''New Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe'' also received positive reviews, with a score of 80, according to Metacritic.<ref name=\"mc_ns_review\"/>\n\n=== Sales ===\n\n{{As of|2019|03|31|df=US}}, ''New Super Mario Bros. U'' has worldwide sales of 5.79 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/sales/software/wiiu.html|title=Top Selling Software Sales Units - Nintendo Wii U Software|website=Nintendo|date=March 31, 2019|accessdate=April 25, 2019}}\n</ref>\n\n''New Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe'' yielded sales of 455,006 physical copies within its first month on sale in Japan, outperforming its Wii U counterpart.<ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://gematsu.com/2019/02/media-create-sales-2-18-19-2-24-19|title=Media Create Sales: 2/18/19 \u2013 2/24/19|website=Gematsu|date=February 27, 2019|accessdate=February 27, 2019}}\n</ref> As of December 2019, it has sold over 747,589 physical copies in Japan.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gematsu.com/2020/01/famitsu-sales-12-23-19-12-29-19 |title=Famitsu Sales: 12/23/19 \u2013 12/29/19 [Update] |website=Gematsu |first=Sal |last=Romano |date=January 8, 2020 |accessdate=January 13, 2020}}</ref> ''Deluxe'' also debuted at the top of the charts in the United Kingdom, selling 56% more copies in its first week than when the Wii U version launched, and remained the UK's best-selling game in its second week on sale.<ref>\n{{cite web|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2019/01/uk_charts_new_super_mario_bros_u_deluxe_launch_sales_24_8_percent_higher_than_on_wii_u_hits_number_one|title=UK Charts: New Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe Launch Sales 24.8% Higher Than On Wii U, Hits Number One|website=Nintendo Life|date=January 14, 2019|accessdate=January 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190122044008/http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2019/01/uk_charts_new_super_mario_bros_u_deluxe_launch_sales_24_8_percent_higher_than_on_wii_u_hits_number_one|archive-date=2019-01-22|url-status=live}}\n</ref><ref>\n{{cite web|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2019/01/uk_charts_new_super_mario_bros_u_deluxe_fights_off_ace_combat_7_to_stay_at_number_one|title=UK Charts: New Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe Fights Off Ace Combat 7 To Stay At Number One|website=Nintendo Life|date=January 21, 2019|accessdate=January 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190122043914/http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2019/01/uk_charts_new_super_mario_bros_u_deluxe_fights_off_ace_combat_7_to_stay_at_number_one|archive-date=2019-01-22|url-status=live}}\n</ref> As of December 2019, ''Deluxe'' has sold 5.85 million copies worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/index.html |title=IR Information : Sales Data - Top Selling Title Sales Units |website=[[Nintendo]] |date=December 31, 2019 |accessdate=January 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Awards ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\" 90%\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Recipient(s)\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2012\n|[[Spike Video Game Awards]]\n|Best Wii/Wii U Game\n|[[Shigeru Miyamoto]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|NintendoLife\n|Wii U Retail Game of 2012\n|rowspan=\"4\"|N/A\n|{{won}}<ref>\n{{cite web | url=http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2012/12/game_of_the_year_nintendo_lifes_staff_awards_2012 | title=Game of the Year: Nintendo Life's Staff Awards 2012 | publisher=NintendoLife | accessdate=January 16, 2013 | author=Whitehead, Thomas | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130102135534/http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2012/12/game_of_the_year_nintendo_lifes_staff_awards_2012 | archive-date=2013-01-02 | url-status=live }}\n</ref>\n|-\n|Vooks.net\n|Game of the Year\n|{{won}}<ref>\n{{cite web | url=http://www.vooks.net/vooks-game-of-the-year-2012-new-super-mario-bros-u/ | title=Vooks Game of the Year 2012: New Super Mario Bros. U | publisher=Vooks.Net | accessdate=June 20, 2013 | author=Vuckovic, Daniel | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130102193139/http://www.vooks.net/vooks-game-of-the-year-2012-new-super-mario-bros-u/ | archive-date=2013-01-02 | url-status=live }}\n</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[IGN]]'s Best of 2012\n|Best Wii U/Wii Game\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|Best Wii U/Wii Multiplayer Game\n|{{Nominated}}\n|} {{Clear}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website}}\n\n{{Super Mario}}\n{{Portal bar|Video games|Japan}}\n\n[[Category:2012 video games]]\n[[Category:2019 video games]]\n[[Category:Asymmetrical multiplayer video games]]\n[[Category:Cooperative video games]]\n[[Category:Mario platform games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Entertainment Planning & Development games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Network games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch eShop games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch games]]\n[[Category:Side-scrolling video games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Japan]]\n[[Category:Video game sequels]]\n[[Category:Video games with 2.5D graphics]]\n[[Category:Video games with downloadable content]]\n[[Category:Video games with expansion packs]]\n[[Category:Wii U eShop games]]\n[[Category:Wii U games]]\n[[Category:Super Mario]]\n[[Category:Video games scored by Mahito Yokota]]\n", "name_user": "Tanonero", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eNew Super Mario Bros. U Deluxe:removed space", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Super_Mario_Bros._U"}
